Aim: finding threshold of images

1. Program to Find the Threshold of an Grayscale Image B] Program to Find the Threshold of an RGB Image

Code :-  
% Read the input image  
originalImage = imread('beamer.jpg'); % Make sure beamer.jpg exists in your folder  
% Convert the image to grayscale (if it's not already)  
grayImage = rgb2gray(originalImage);  
% Display the original grayscale image

figure;  
imshow(grayImage);  
title('Original Grayscale Image');  
% Determine the threshold using Otsu's method  
threshold = graythresh(grayImage);  
binaryImage = imbinarize(grayImage, threshold);  
figure;  
imshow(binaryImage);  
title('Binary Image (Thresholded)');  
rgbImage = imread('beamer.jpg');  
% Display the original RGB image

figure;  
imshow(rgbImage);  
title('Original RGB Image');  
% Convert the RGB image to grayscale  
grayImage = rgb2gray(rgbImage);  
% Determine the threshold using Otsu's method  
threshold = graythresh(grayImage);
% Convert the grayscale image to binary  
binaryImage = imbinarize(grayImage, threshold);  
% Display the binary image  
figure;  
imshow(binaryImage);  
title('Binary Image (Thresholded)');  

